Target: An ontology developed for representing Metal-Organic Polyhedra (MOPs).

Comment: A molecular cage is chemical species that has a dimensional chamber (i.e. cavity) surrounded by a molecular framework. It is a form of a polyatomic entity.
A coordination cage is a molecular cage comprised of metal-based and organic building units.  A metal-organic cage (MOC) may be a synonym for coordination cage.
A metal-organic polyhedron (MOP) is a highly symmetrical coordination cage.
Cavity is the interior void in a molecular cage.
An amount of space, in the context defined by a molecular cage cavity.
An assembly model represent a spatial constract (i.e. skeleton) of discrete and well-defined interacting generic building units. Many chemical structures may share same assembly model.

Generic Building Unit is a modular entity that is able to connect to other generic units, leading to a variety of assembly models. The generic building unit has a unique modularity and spatial connectivity.
A generic building unit number provides the number of copies of generic units present in a particular assembly model.
A chemical building unit is a  virtual molecular fragment or a real chemical compound that participates in the construction of larger complex assemblies such as molecular cages.
A binding site is the segment of the building unit that involves in chemical reactivity and enhances the interlocking between different building blocks.
A binding direction specifies the orientation of the binding site with respect to the overall building unit core.
A polyhedral shape refers to the shape of a solid defined by many plane faces
An organic site is a form of a binding site that is made of orgnaic functional groups (e.g. carboxylate, pyridine, bypiridine etc).
A metal-based site is a form of binding site that is typically made of electrophilic metal centres. A label to the metal site may be the type of the element (e.g. V, Fe, Zn etc.).
Sideway binding occurs when the direction of the coordination of the binding site is not alligned is in a straight line from the central core of the building unit and point sto the side.
Direct binding occurs when the direction of the coordination of the binding site is alligned is in a straight line from the central core of the building unit.
A provenance refers to the journal article where a particular MOP has been reported.
A relation betwenn  a MOP and its building unit.
A relation between a molecular entity and the formal charge associated with it.
A relation depicting to which assembly model a particular metal organic polyhedron belongs to.
A relation between molecular cages and the exisitence of within the molecular cages.
A relation between a molecular cage and the literature where such cage has been reported.
A relation between a cavity of a cage and the amount of space referring to the volume.
A relation between a the chemical assembly model the number of generic units constructing that assembly model.
A relation between the chemical assembly model and the constituting generic buildinng unit.
A relation between an assembly mode MOP and its most basic polyhedral shape addopted by that MOP.
A relation defining the orientation between a binding unit in respect to the propagation of the building unit core.
A relation between the building unit and the type of associated binding sites.
A relation that connects the number of generic units with the type of the generic unit.
A relation that connects the chemical building unit and the more abstract generic building unit.
A relation between a molecular entity and its molecular weight.
Data string outlying the formula of the chemical building unit.
A data property that informs on the exact deposition number of the MOP in the CCDC database.
A relation between a molecular entity and the geometry associated with it.
The number of generic building units that connect to a selected generic building.
Description of how the other beneric building units are spatially oriented arround the building unit of interst. (e.g. linear, bent, off-set, pyramidal, planar).
A relation between chemcial species and their idealised symmetry pointgroup.
DOI number provided as an identifier not as a link.
A data property describing polyhedral shape through a letter code.
